stem</title><link href="https://chrissunny94.github.io/blog/blog/2024/rotations-and-coordinate-system/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Rotations and coordinate system"/><published>2024-03-10T02:12:32+00:00</published><updated>2024-03-10T02:12:32+00:00</updated><id>https://chrissunny94.github.io/blog/blog/2024/rotations-and-coordinate-system</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://chrissunny94.github.io/blog/blog/2024/rotations-and-coordinate-system/"><![CDATA[]]></content><author><name></name></author></entry><entry><title type="html">In the end My Immaculate Heart will Triumph</title><link href="https://chrissunny94.github.io/blog/blog/2023/in-the-end-my-immaculate-heart-will-triumph/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="In the end My Immaculate Heart will Triumph"/><published>2023-10-04T09:02:48+00:00</published><updated>2023-10-04T09:02:48+00:00</updated><id>https://chrissunny94.github.io/blog/blog/2023/in-the-end-my-immaculate-heart-will-triumph</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://chrissunny94.github.io/blog/blog/2023/in-the-end-my-immaculate-heart-will-triumph/"><![CDATA[]]></content><author><name></name></author></entry><entry><title type="html">Object tracking In Camera and PointCloud a comparisson</title><link href="https://chrissunny94.github.io/blog/blog/2023/object-tracking-in-camera-and-pointcloud-a-comparisson/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Object tracking In Camera and PointCloud a comparisson"/><published>2023-09-07T05:24:30+00:00</published><updated>2023-09-07T05:24:30+00:00</updated><id>https://chrissunny94.github.io/blog/blog/2023/object-tracking-in-camera-and-pointcloud-a-comparisson</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://chrissunny94.github.io/blog/blog/2023/object-tracking-in-camera-and-pointcloud-a-comparisson/"><![CDATA[]]></content><author><name></name></author></entry><entry><title type="html">Deep Learning with PointCloud, Image and different kind of sensor fusion</title><link href="https://chrissunny94.github.io/blog/blog/2023/deep-learning-with-pointcloud-image-and-different-kind-of-sensor-fusion/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Deep Learning with PointCloud, Image and different kind of sensor fusion"/><published>2023-09-06T05:20:30+00:00</published><updated>2023-09-06T05:20:30+00:00</updated><id>https://chrissunny94.github.io/blog/blog/2023/deep-learning-with-pointcloud-image-and-different-kind-of-sensor-fusion</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://chrissunny94.github.io/blog/blog/2023/deep-learning-with-pointcloud-image-and-different-kind-of-sensor-fusion/"><![CDATA[]]></content><author><name></name></author></entry><entry><title type="html">LIDAR and Pointcloud Simple tutorial for OP</title><link href="https://chrissunny94.github.io/blog/blog/2023/lidar-and-pointcloud-simple-tutorial-for-op/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="LIDAR and Pointcloud Simple tutorial for OP"/><published>2023-09-05T09:22:49+00:00</published><updated>2023-09-05T09:22:49+00:00</updated><id>https://chrissunny94.github.io/blog/blog/2023/lidar-and-pointcloud-simple-tutorial-for-op</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://chrissunny94.github.io/blog/blog/2023/lidar-and-pointcloud-simple-tutorial-for-op/"><![CDATA[]]></content><author><name></name></author></entry><entry><title type="html">Lidar SLAM comparison</title><link href="https://chrissunny94.github.io/blog/blog/2023/lidar-slam-comparison/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Lidar SLAM comparison"/><published>2023-08-01T03:59:33+00:00</published><updated>2023-08-01T03:59:33+00:00</updated><id>https://chrissunny94.github.io/blog/blog/2023/lidar-slam-comparison</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://chrissunny94.github.io/blog/blog/2023/lidar-slam-comparison/"><![CDATA[]]></content><author><name></name></author></entry><entry><title type="html">a post with jupyter notebook</title><link href="https://chrissunny94.github.io/blog/blog/2023/jupyter-notebook/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="a post with jupyter notebook"/><published>2023-07-04T12:57:00+00:00</published><updated>2023-07-04T12:57:00+00:00</updated><id>https://chrissunny94.github.io/blog/blog/2023/jupyter-notebook</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://chrissunny94.github.io/blog/blog/2023/jupyter-notebook/"><![CDATA[<p>To include a jupyter notebook in a post, you can use the following code:</p> <div class="language-html highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>{::nomarkdown}
{% assign jupyter_path = "assets/jupyter/blog.ipynb" | relative_url %}
{% capture notebook_exists %}{% file_exists assets/jupyter/blog.ipynb %}{% endcapture %}
{% if notebook_exists == "true" %}
    {% jupyter_notebook jupyter_path %}
{% else %}
    <span class="nt">&lt;p&gt;</span>Sorry, the notebook you are looking for does not exist.<span class="nt">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
{% endif %}
{:/nomarkdown}
</code></pre></div></div> <p>Let’s break it down: this is possible thanks to <a href="https://github.com/red-data-tools/jekyll-jupyter-notebook">Jekyll Jupyter Notebook plugin</a> that allows you to embed jupyter notebooks in your posts. It basically calls <a href="https://nbconvert.readthedocs.io/en/latest/usage.html#convert-html"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">jupyter nbconvert --to html</code></a> to convert the notebook to an html page and then includes it in the post. Since <a href="https://jekyllrb.com/docs/configuration/markdown/">Kramdown</a> is the default Markdown renderer for Jekyll, we need to surround the call to the plugin with the <a href="https://kramdown.gettalong.org/syntax.html#extensions">::nomarkdown</a> tag so that it stops processing this part with Kramdown and outputs the content as-is.</p> <p>The plugin takes as input the path to the notebook, but it assumes the file exists. If you want to check if the file exists before calling the plugin, you can use the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">file_exists</code> filter. This avoids getting a 404 error from the plugin and ending up displaying the main page inside of it instead. If the file does not exist, you can output a message to the user. The code displayed above outputs the following:</p> <div class="jupyter-notebook" style="position: relative; width: 100%; margin: 0 auto;"> <div class="jupyter-notebook-iframe-container"> <iframe src="/blog/assets/jupyter/blog.ipynb.html" style="position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; border-style: none;" width="100%" height="100%" onload="this.parentElement.style.paddingBottom = (this.contentWindow.document.documentElement.scrollHeight + 10) + 'px'"></iframe> </div> </div> <p>Note that the jupyter notebook supports both light and dark themes.</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="sample-posts"/><category term="formatting"/><category term="jupyter"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[an example of a blog post with jupyter notebook]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">a post with videos</title><link href="https://chrissunny94.github.io/blog/blog/2023/videos/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="a post with videos"/><published>2023-04-24T21:01:00+00:00</published><updated>2023-04-24T21:01:00+00:00</updated><id>https://chrissunny94.github.io/blog/blog/2023/videos</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://chrissunny94.github.io/blog/blog/2023/videos/"><![CDATA[<p>This is an example post with videos. It supports local video files.</p> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <video src="/blog/assets/video/pexels-engin-akyurt-6069112-960x540-30fps.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" autoplay="" controls=""/> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <video src="/blog/assets/video/pexels-engin-akyurt-6069112-960x540-30fps.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" controls=""/> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="caption"> A simple, elegant caption looks good between video rows, after each row, or doesn't have to be there at all. </div> <p>It does also support embedding videos from different sources. Here are some examples:</p> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/jNQXAC9IVRw" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen="" width="auto" height="auto"/> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/524933864?h=1ac4fd9fb4&amp;title=0&amp;byline=0&amp;portrait=0" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen="" width="auto" height="auto"/> </figure> </div> </div>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="sample-posts"/><category term="formatting"/><category term="videos"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[this is what included videos could look like]]></summary></entry></feed>